This paper proposes a new approach to a value network architecture for the game Go, which involves training different values simultaneously for different settings of komi. This involves the use of machine learning techniques such as deep neural networks, which are commonly used in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of computer vision techniques to analyze the game board, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of game theory to balance the initiative of playing first, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper proposes a new dynamic komi method to improve game-playing strength, which involves the use of reinforcement learning techniques, which fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
